context_notes.note:
Vikunja's REST API uses PUT for create and POST for update (reversed from REST convention).
This is already handled correctly in server.py — the bridge daemon must follow the same pattern:
- Create task: PUT /api/v1/projects/{project_id}/tasks
- Update task: POST /api/v1/tasks/{task_id}
- Create comment: PUT /api/v1/tasks/{task_id}/comments
- Complete task: POST /api/v1/tasks/{task_id} with {"done": true}
